%
% OCTAVE REFERENCE (concert pitch):
%   ABC letter (no comma/apostrophe) = 4th octave: C=C4, D=D4 ... B=B4
%   One comma lower: C,=C3, D,=D3 ... B,=B3
%   Two commas:      C,,=C2 etc.
%   One apostrophe:  c=C5, d=D5 ... (or use lowercase for 5th octave)
%   In ABC: uppercase = octave 4, lowercase = octave 5
%
%   TENOR VOICES (transpose=-12): written pitch sounds one octave lower.
%   To sound concert X, write X one octave higher.
%     Written B  (B4)  = sounds B3   Written d  (D5)  = sounds D4
%     Written A  (A4)  = sounds A3   Written e  (E5)  = sounds E4
%     Written G  (G4)  = sounds G3   Written f  (F5)  = sounds F4
%     Written F  (F4)  = sounds F3   Written g  (G5)  = sounds G4
%     Written E  (E4)  = sounds E3
%     Written D  (D4)  = sounds D3   (lowest practical for T1 range B2)
%     Written C  (C4)  = sounds C3
%
%   BARITONE (bass clef, concert pitch):
%     E,,=E2  A,,=A2  C,=C3  D,=D3  F,=F3  A,=A3  C=C4
%
%   BASS I (bass clef, concert pitch):
%     D,,=D2  A,,=A2  B,,=B2  D,=D3  A,=A3
%
